<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>ChanceProb</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>ChanceProb</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>ChanceProb</refname>
<refpurpose>
Returns the probability an action is chosen by nature
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
ChanceProb[action->ACTION] =: NUMBER 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>ChanceProb</function> returns the probability of 
<parameter>action</parameter> being chosen at its information
set by the chance player.  It is an error if <parameter>action</parameter>
is not an action
which is chosen by the chance player.
</para>
</refsect1>

